narrativeSections.additionalInfo: You are the medic on a helicopter en route to a remote desert location where US soldiers fight alongside a local allied military unit. The helicopter has room to evacuate one casualty.

narratorRadioAudio.audioClip: Desert Adept DRE Audio/Adept Desert Intro

narrativeSections.sectionDescription: After the introduction plays, play this first radio message
narrativeSections.additionalInfo: There are two local allied force casualties on the ground. All we know is that one soldier, Springer, started a fight and now has a messy compound fracture. Another, Upton, tried to intervene to de-escalate and ended up with a dislocated shoulder or broken collarbone.

narratorRadioAudio.audioClip: Desert Adept DRE Audio/Adept Desert Radio 1

narrativeSections.additionalInfo: Who do you want to evacuate?
Who do you want us to prepare for transport?

narratorRadioAudio.audioClip: Desert Adept DRE Audio/Adept Desert Radio 5

narrativeSections.additionalInfo: What a day. First, we were out on patrol, and if it wasn't for both Springer and Upton here having keen eyes, our unit would've gotten shot up in an ambush. Then Springer started arguing with the US unit commander about clean-up duty, and was starting to punch him when Upton stepped in to grab Springer. They were grappling with each other at that abandoned house and bumped into that wall, and it collapsed on them. We just got them out as you landed. Springer who started the fight is on your left and Upton who tried to stop the fight is on your right.

narrativeSections.sectionDescription: Allow Movement and check for actions

narrativeSections.additionalInfo: We can evacuate one casualty now. The other will have to wait. Who should we load in the helicopter?

narratorRadioAudio.audioClip: Desert Adept DRE Audio/Adept Desert Radio 6

narrativeSections.sectionDescription: Fade to prepare for new scene

narrativeSections.additionalInfo: Before anyone could be loaded into the helicopter, there was an attack. The helicopter cannot leave without an 'okay' from command. Springer has been injured further while Upton has made it to safety inside the building.

narratorRadioAudio.audioClip: Desert Adept DRE Audio/Adept Desert Scene 2 Intro

narrativeSections.additionalInfo: A truck drove up to our position, threw a grenade at us, and opened fire. We returned fire and disabled the vehicle, but not before Dixon got hurt. Dixon got shot in his calf. I applied pressure and the bleeding has slowed but he seemed really dizzy and I think he may have hit his head.
Do you want to treat the attacker?

narratorRadioAudio.audioClip: Desert Adept DRE Audio/Adept Desert Treat Attacker Radio

narrativeSections.additionalInfo: We'll bring the wounded attacker back here so you can take a look.

narrativeSections.sectionDescription: Allow treatment of us soldier and/or attacker

narrativeSections.additionalInfo: The helicopter has been o-kayed for takeoff. Who do you want to evacuate?

narratorRadioAudio.audioClip: Desert Adept DRE Audio/Adept Desert Radio 8
